itemDescription: third child and eldest daughter of Edward VII of the United Kingdom and Alexandra of Denmark

wikipedia_page.main: Louise, Princess Royal and Duchess of Fife  (Louise Victoria Alexandra Dagmar; 20 February 1867 – 4 January 1931) was the third child and eldest daughter of King Edward VII and Queen Alexandra of the United Kingdom; she was a younger sister of King George V. Louise was given the title of Princess Royal in 1905. Known by her shy and quiet personality, Louise remained a low-key member of the royal family throughout her life.
